      "content": "i get what u mean about them being \"distinct,\" but if u look at history, isn't it pretty obvious that the more \"civilized\" groups are the ones that ended up dominating and shaping the world? like, if a culture doesn't develop things like permanent cities or organized religion/statehood, don't they basically just get absorbed or replaced by the more \"advanced\" ones? it feels like there's a natural hierarchy of how much a society can actually achieve based on how far they've moved past that subsistence stage.",
